cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the secrecy capacity region of the broadcast channel, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on physical layer security and proposes feedback coding schemes to enhance it, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication systems and their down-link, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a hybrid coding scheme that uses feedback to generate cooperative messages, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed feedback schemes via two examples, which could involve multimedia data transmission.
